  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best pre workout drink before a long run?",
  "response": "Choosing the best pre-workout drink before a long run depends on your individual preferences, dietary needs, and personal goals. Here are some options that are commonly recommended:\n\n1. **Electrolyte Drinks**: Drinks like Gatorade or Nuun tablets mixed with water can help replenish electrolytes lost through sweat and provide carbohydrates for energy.\n\n2. **Coconut Water**: A natural source of electrolytes that offers hydration without added sugars and artificial ingredients.\n\n3. **Homemade Sports Drink**: You can make your own by mixing water, a small amount of salt, a splash of fruit juice for flavor, and perhaps some honey or maple syrup for carbohydrates.\n\n4. **BCAA (Branched Chain Amino Acids) Drinks**: These can help reduce muscle fatigue and may enhance endurance.\n\n5. **Coffee or Caffeinated Beverages**: For many runners, a cup of coffee or a caffeinated sports drink can increase endurance and focus during runs.\n\n6. **Beetroot Juice**: Some studies suggest that beetroot juice can improve exercise performance due to its high nitrates, which may help improve blood flow.\n\n7. **Protein Smoothie**: A light smoothie made with protein powder, a banana, and some almond milk can provide a good balance of carbs and protein for longer runs.\n\n8. **Carbohydrate Gels**: While not a drink per se, these can be taken before the run to provide a concentrated source of carbohydrates.\n\nWhen choosing a drink, consider the following:\n\n- **Timing**: Consume your pre-workout drink about 30-60 minutes before your run.\n- **Hydration**: Make sure you're well-hydrated leading up to your run.\n- **Trial & Error**: It\u2019s important to test different drinks during training runs to see what works best for your digestive system and performance.\n\nUltimately, the best choice is one that works for your body and helps you feel energized and hydrated for your long run.",
